cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DS

The paper proposes a fast active learning algorithm for regression, tailored for neural network models. The algorithm is based on uncertainty estimation from stochastic dropout output of the network. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning architectures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The experiments involve both synthetic and real-world datasets, which could place the paper in cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
